W. 146th Street, north side, east from Seventh, to Lenox Avenues, and showing the demolition of portions of the old N- York Railway -company carbarn. This structure was sold for $250,000 to the New York Central Omnibus Gorp. according to the New York Times of May 24, 1938 and will be replaced with a one story garage. The apartment shown at the right is at the N.E.
corner of Seventh Avenue and is not included.
August 17, 1938.
P.L. Sperr
